{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870572553,"sessionID":"ses_285e13ecaffeMp9o3UxFFIXU67","part":{"id":"prt_d7a22735d001GIuNq3q3oeMjMd","messageID":"msg_d7a225cf7001neUFjYw8W3JQWZ","sessionID":"ses_285e13ecaffeMp9o3UxFFIXU67","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_921a36c29ae94ceeafa4f373","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n2: \n3: **Module:** manifests\n4: **Language:** YAML\n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: Provide the complete Helm chart (`manifests/charts/base`) for deploying the AgentCube control-plane stack on Kubernetes. This includes parameterized templates for Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano agent scheduler, RBAC resources, CRDs, and a comprehensive `values.yaml` that drives all configurable aspects (images, replicas, resources, Redis connectivity, environment overrides). The chart enables one-command installation and upgrade of AgentCube with environment-specific customization, eliminating manual YAML editing.\n10: \n11: ## Scope\n12: \n13: ### In Scope\n14: \n15: - `Chart.yaml` — chart metadata (`apiVersion: v1`, name `agentcube`, version `0.1.0`, appVersion `1.0.0`)\n16: - `values.yaml` — full key tree with typed defaults for all components:\n17:   - Global: `imagePullSecrets`, `nameOverride`, `fullnameOverride`\n18:   - Redis: `redis.addr`, `redis.password` (empty-string defaults; user must supply at install time)\n19:   - Router: `router.replicas`, `router.image` (repo/pullPolicy/tag), `router.service` (type/port/targetPort), `router.resources` (limits/requests), `router.config`, `router.extraEnv`, `router.serviceAccountName`, `router.rbac.create`\n20:   - Workload Manager: `workloadmanager.replicas`, `workloadmanager.image`, `workloadmanager.service`, `workloadmanager.resources`, `workloadmanager.extraEnv`\n21:   - Volcano scheduler: `volcano.scheduler.enabled`, `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, `volcano.scheduler.image`\n22: - Template: `workloadmanager.yaml` — Deployment + Service with health probes (`/health`), Redis env vars, `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` fieldRef, `extraEnv` support, resource requests/limits from values\n23: - Template: `agentcube-router.yaml` — Deployment + Service with health probes (`/health/live`, `/health/ready`), `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` auto-resolution via in-cluster DNS, `extraEnv`, conditional `serviceAccountName`\n24: - Template: `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` — ServiceAccount, ClusterRole (agent-sandbox CRDs, AgentCube CRDs, core workloads, auth, secrets), ClusterRoleBinding\n25: - Template: `rbac-router.yaml` — conditional namespace-scoped ServiceAccount/Role/RoleBinding for Router secret management (gated by `router.rbac.create`)\n26: - Template: `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` — conditional ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment (gated by `volcano.scheduler.enabled`)\n27: - CRDs: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` and `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` under `crds/` directory (API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1`, scope `Namespaced`)\n28: - Install command pattern: `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace --set redis.addr=... --set redis.password=...`\n29: \n30: ### Out of Scope\n31: \n32: - Dockerfile definitions for workloadmanager, router, picod images (covered by deployment spec)\n33: - Makefile build/docker/e2e targets (covered by deployment spec)\n34: - E2E test infrastructure and Kind cluster provisioning\n35: - Python SDK, CLI tooling, sandbox orchestration code\n36: - Volcano scheduler installation outside of the optional chart toggle\n37: - External Redis/Valkey deployment (only connectivity configuration)\n38: \n39: ## Architecture Summary\n40: \n41: ```\n42: manifests/charts/base/\n43: ├── Chart.yaml                          # Chart metadata\n44: ├── values.yaml                         # Default configuration values\n45: ├── crds/\n46: │   ├── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n47: │   └── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n48: └── templates/\n49:     ├── workloadmanager.yaml            # WM Deployment + Service\n50:     ├── agentcube-router.yaml           # Router Deployment + Service\n51:     ├── rbac/\n52:     │   └── workloadmanager.yaml        # WM SA + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding\n53:     ├── rbac-router.yaml                # Optional Router SA + Role + RoleBinding\n54:     └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Optional Volcano scheduler\n55: ```\n56: \n57: **Component deployment shape:**\n58: \n59: | Component | Kind | Service | Port | Health |\n60: |-----------|------|---------|------|--------|\n61: | Workload Manager | Deployment + Service | `workloadmanager` | 8080 | `GET /health` (liveness 10s, readiness 5s) |\n62: | Router | Deployment + Service | `agentcube-router` | 8080 | `GET /health/live` + `/health/ready` (1s initial, 2s period) |\n63: | Volcano Scheduler (optional) | Deployment + Service | `volcano-agent-scheduler-service` | 8080 | — |\n64: \n65: **Environment variable injection:**\n66: \n67: | Component | Env Var | Source |\n68: |-----------|---------|--------|\n69: | All | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | `metadata.namespace` (fieldRef) |\n70: | WM, Router | `REDIS_ADDR` | `redis.addr` values |\n71: | WM, Router | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | `redis.password` values |\n72: | Router | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Auto-resolved: `http://workloadmanager.<ns>.svc.cluster.local:<port>` |\n73: | WM | `extraEnv` entries | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` values |\n74: | Router | `extraEnv` entries | `router.extraEnv` values |\n75: \n76: **RBAC matrix:**\n77: \n78: | Resource | Scope | Conditional | Grants |\n79: |----------|-------|-------------|--------|\n80: | WM ClusterRole | Cluster | Always | agent-sandbox CRDs, AgentCube CRDs (`codeinterpreters`, `agentruntimes`), pods, secrets, tokenreviews |\n81: | Router Role | Namespace | `router.rbac.create` | secrets (full verbs) |\n82: | Volcano ClusterRole | Cluster | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | CRDs, events, pods, bindings, PV/PVC, nodes, leases, resourceclaims, nodeshards |\n83: \n84: ## Impact Analysis\n85: \n86: | Area | Impact |\n87: |------|--------|\n88: | **Consumers** | All deployment workflows (E2E tests, production installs, developer local Kind clusters) depend on this chart |\n89: | **Backward compatibility** | New chart; no existing manifests to migrate. Future changes to `values.yaml` keys are breaking for downstream values files |\n90: | **Dependencies** | Helm 3, Kubernetes 1.28+, Redis/Valkey instance (external), optional Volcano scheduler image |\n91: | **Security** | WM runs as non-root (`apiserver` UID 1000); Router runs as non-root (`router` UID 1000); ClusterRole grants broad permissions (secrets CRUD, sandbox CRDs) — least-privilege review recommended; auth token review via `TokenReview` API |\n92: | **Performance** | Default 1 replica per component; resource requests (100m CPU, 128Mi memory) and limits (500m CPU, 512Mi memory) prevent resource starvation; horizontal scaling via `replicas` values |\n93: | **Operational** | `extraEnv` arrays allow runtime tuning without chart changes; `image.tag` overrides enable canary/rollback workflows |\n94: \n95: ## Alternatives Considered\n96: \n97: | Alternative | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n98: |-------------|------|------|----------|\n99: | **Raw Kubernetes YAML manifests** | No Helm dependency; simple `kubectl apply` | No parameterization; environment-specific diffs require manual editing or kustomize overlays; no `helm upgrade` rollback | Rejected — Helm provides values-driven customization and lifecycle management |\n100: | **Kustomize overlays** | Native kubectl support; patch-based customization | More complex for multi-environment; no built-in rollback; values not centralized in a single file | Rejected — Helm values.yaml provides a single source of truth for all configurable parameters |\n101: | **Helm with subcharts (wm + router as separate charts)** | Independent lifecycle per component; versioning isolation | Adds complexity for a tightly coupled control plane; shared values (Redis, namespace) require parent chart coordination | Rejected — single chart matches the coupled deployment model; subcharts can be introduced later if components decouple |\n102: | **Operator-based deployment** | Declarative CRD-driven lifecycle; automatic reconciliation | Significant development overhead; overkill for initial deployment; Helm is sufficient for stateless control-plane components | Deferred — consider if AgentCube adopts GitOps patterns requiring custom operators |\n103: | **Helm `apiVersion: v2` (Helm 3)** | Library chart support, better dependency management | `apiVersion: v1` is sufficient for current scope; migration path exists | Deferred — use `v1` now, upgrade to `v2` if subchart/library dependencies are added |\n104: \n105: ## Upstream Dependencies\n106: \n107: - Helm 3 (chart packaging and installation)\n108: - Kubernetes API server (CRD registration, Deployment/Service/RBAC creation)\n109: - Redis/Valkey service (external; address and password supplied via values)\n110: - Container images: `workloadmanager`, `agentcube-router`, optional `vc-agent-scheduler` (built via Makefile Docker targets)\n111: - agent-sandbox CRDs (external dependency; WM ClusterRole references `agents.x-k8s.io` and `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` API groups)\n112: \n113: ## Status\n114: \n115: - [ ] Proposal review\n116: - [ ] Implementation\n117: - [ ] Verification\n\n(End of file - total 117 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n**Module:** manifests\n**Language:** YAML\n**Size:** L\n\n## Purpose\n\nProvide the complete Helm chart (`manifests/charts/base`) for deploying the AgentCube control-plane stack on Kubernetes. This includes parameterized templates for Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano agent scheduler, RBAC resources, CRDs, and a comprehensive `values.yaml` that drives all configurable aspects (images, replicas, resources, Redis connectivity, environment overrides). The chart enables one-command installation and upgrade of AgentCube with environment-specific customization, eliminating manual YAML editing.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n- `Chart.yaml` — chart metadata (`apiVersion: v1`, name `agentcube`, version `0.1.0`, appVersion `1.0.0`)\n- `values.yaml` — full key tree with typed defaults for all components:\n  - Global: `imagePullSecrets`, `nameOverride`, `fullnameOverride`\n  - Redis: `redis.addr`, `redis.password` (empty-string defaults; user must supply at install time)\n  - Router: `router.replicas`, `router.image` (repo/pullPolicy/tag), `router.service` (type/port/targetPort), `router.resources` (limits/requests), `router.config`, `router.extraEnv`, `router.serviceAccountName`, `router.rbac.create`\n  - Workload Manager: `workloadmanager.replicas`, `workloadmanager.image`, `workloadmanager.service`, `workloadmanager.resources`, `workloadmanager.extraEnv`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775870572545,"end":1775870572552}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870573904,"sessionID":"ses_285e13ecaffeMp9o3UxFFIXU67","part":{"id":"prt_d7a227892001KXG5g79mH7U27c","messageID":"msg_d7a225cf7001neUFjYw8W3JQWZ","sessionID":"ses_285e13ecaffeMp9o3UxFFIXU67","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02d88ecb65344f6fb2b71c85","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `manifests`\n6: - **Language:** YAML\n7: - **Size:** L\n8: - **Base specs:** `deployment/spec.md`, `deployment/design.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: Chart.yaml metadata\n13: \n14: The chart SHALL define `Chart.yaml` with `apiVersion: v1`, `name: agentcube`, `version: 0.1.0`, and `appVersion: 1.0.0`.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Chart metadata fields are correct\n17: - **GIVEN** the file `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` exists\n18: - **WHEN** it is parsed as YAML\n19: - **THEN** `apiVersion` equals `v1`, `name` equals `agentcube`, `version` equals `0.1.0`, and `appVersion` equals `1.0.0`\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Helm lint passes on chart metadata\n22: - **GIVEN** a valid `Chart.yaml` with the fields above\n23: - **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is run\n24: - **THEN** no errors or warnings related to chart metadata are reported\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ### Requirement: values.yaml default key tree\n29: \n30: The chart SHALL provide a `values.yaml` with the full key tree documented in the deployment design, including typed defaults for `imagePullSecrets`, `nameOverride`, `fullnameOverride`, `redis.addr`, `redis.password`, `router` (replicas, image, service, resources, config, extraEnv, serviceAccountName, rbac), `workloadmanager` (replicas, image, service, resources, extraEnv), and `volcano.scheduler` (enabled, replicas, image). Comments SHALL state that Redis settings must be provided by the user during installation.\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Default values are valid YAML\n33: - **GIVEN** the file `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml`\n34: - **WHEN** it is parsed as YAML\n35: - **THEN** no parse errors occur and all top-level keys (`imagePullSecrets`, `nameOverride`, `fullnameOverride`, `redis`, `router`, `workloadmanager`, `volcano`) are present\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Redis defaults are empty strings with comments\n38: - **GIVEN** `values.yaml` is rendered\n39: - **WHEN** `redis.addr` and `redis.password` are read\n40: - **THEN** both default to `\"\"` and comments indicate they must be provided at install time\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: Router defaults match design\n43: - **GIVEN** `values.yaml` is rendered\n44: - **WHEN** router values are read\n45: - **THEN** `router.replicas` is `1`, `router.image.repository` is `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router`, `router.image.pullPolicy` is `IfNotPresent`, `router.image.tag` is `latest`, `router.service.type` is `ClusterIP`, `router.service.port` is `8080`, `router.service.targetPort` is `8080`, resource limits are `cpu: 500m, memory: 512Mi`, requests are `cpu: 100m, memory: 128Mi`, `router.rbac.create` is `false`\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Workload Manager defaults match design\n48: - **GIVEN** `values.yaml` is rendered\n49: - **WHEN** workloadmanager values are read\n50: - **THEN** `workloadmanager.replicas` is `1`, `workloadmanager.image.repository` is `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager`, `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` is `IfNotPresent`, `workloadmanager.image.tag` is `latest`, `workloadmanager.service.type` is `ClusterIP`, `workloadmanager.service.port` is `8080`, resource limits are `cpu: 500m, memory: 512Mi`, requests are `cpu: 100m, memory: 128Mi`\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler defaults to disabled\n53: - **GIVEN** `values.yaml` is rendered\n54: - **WHEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is read\n55: - **THEN** it defaults to `false`\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ### Requirement: Workload Manager Deployment template\n60: \n61: The template `workloadmanager.yaml` SHALL render a `Deployment` named `workloadmanager` in `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` with: replicas from `workloadmanager.replicas`; container `workloadmanager` using `repository:tag` with `imagePullPolicy`; port `http` on `workloadmanager.service.port`; env vars `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef `metadata.namespace`), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, plus `workloadmanager.extraEnv`; args `--port=<port>` and `--runtime-class-name=` (empty); resource requests/limits from values; liveness probe HTTP GET `/health` (initialDelay 10s, period 10s); readiness probe HTTP GET `/health` (initialDelay 5s, period 5s); optional `imagePullSecrets`; `serviceAccountName: workloadmanager`.\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: Default deployment renders correctly\n64: - **GIVEN** default values and release namespace `agentcube`\n65: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` is run\n66: - **THEN** the output contains a `Deployment` named `workloadmanager` in namespace `agentcube` with `replicas: 1`, container image `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest`, and `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent`\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: Health probes are configured\n69: - **GIVEN** default values\n70: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n71: - **THEN** the Workload Manager container has liveness probe `httpGet /health` on the service port with `initialDelaySeconds: 10, periodSeconds: 10` and readiness probe `httpGet /health` with `initialDelaySeconds: 5, periodSeconds: 5`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Redis env vars are injected\n74: - **GIVEN** `--set redis.addr=redis.default.svc:6379 --set redis.password=secret123`\n75: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n76: - **THEN** the Workload Manager container env includes `REDIS_ADDR=redis.default.svc:6379` and `REDIS_PASSWORD=secret123`\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE uses fieldRef\n79: - **GIVEN** any valid installation\n80: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n81: - **THEN** the Workload Manager container env includes `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` with `valueFrom.fieldRef.fieldPath: metadata.namespace`\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: extraEnv entries are appended\n84: - **GIVEN** `--set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"CUSTOM_VAR\",\"value\":\"custom-val\"}]'`\n85: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n86: - **THEN** the Workload Manager container env includes `CUSTOM_VAR=custom-val` in addition to the standard env vars\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Container args include port and runtime-class-name\n89: - **GIVEN** `workloadmanager.service.port` is `8080`\n90: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n91: - **THEN** the container args include `--port=8080` and `--runtime-class-name=`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Resource requests and limits from values\n94: - **GIVEN** default values\n95: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n96: - **THEN** the container resources have `requests: {cpu: 100m, memory: 128Mi}` and `limits: {cpu: 500m, memory: 512Mi}`\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Custom replica count\n99: - **GIVEN** `--set workloadmanager.replicas=3`\n100: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n101: - **THEN** the Deployment spec has `replicas: 3`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Custom image override\n104: - **GIVEN** `--set workloadmanager.image.repository=myregistry/workloadmanager --set workloadmanager.image.tag=v1.2.3`\n105: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n106: - **THEN** the container image is `myregistry/workloadmanager:v1.2.3`\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: imagePullSecrets are applied when set\n109: - **GIVEN** `--set-json 'imagePullSecrets=[{\"name\":\"my-secret\"}]'`\n110: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n111: - **THEN** the Deployment `spec.template.spec.imagePullSecrets` includes `{name: my-secret}`\n112: \n113: ---\n114: \n115: ### Requirement: Workload Manager Service template\n116: \n117: The template `workloadmanager.yaml` SHALL render a `Service` named `workloadmanager` in `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` with: `type` from `workloadmanager.service.type`; `port` and `targetPort` from `workloadmanager.service.port`; selector `app: workloadmanager`.\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: Default service renders\n120: - **GIVEN** default values\n121: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n122: - **THEN** a `Service` named `workloadmanager` exists with `type: ClusterIP`, `port: 8080`, `targetPort: 8080`, and selector `app: workloadmanager`\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: Custom service type\n125: - **GIVEN** `--set workloadmanager.service.type=NodePort`\n126: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n127: - **THEN** the Service `type` is `NodePort`\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: Router Deployment template\n132: \n133: The template `agentcube-router.yaml` SHALL render a `Deployment` named `agentcube-router` in `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` with: replicas from `router.replicas`; conditional `serviceAccountName` if `router.serviceAccountName` is non-empty; container `agentcube-router` using `router.image`; container port `router.service.targetPort`; env vars `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, plus `router.extraEnv`; args `--port=<targetPort>` and `--debug`; resources from values; liveness probe `/health/live` and readiness probe `/health/ready` on targetPort (initialDelay 1s, period 2s); optional `imagePullSecrets`.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Default router deployment renders\n136: - **GIVEN** default values and release namespace `agentcube`\n137: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` is run\n138: - **THEN** the output contains a `Deployment` named `agentcube-router` in namespace `agentcube` with `replicas: 1` and image `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router:latest`\n139: \n140: #### Scenario: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL resolves via in-cluster DNS\n141: - **GIVEN** release namespace `agentcube` and `workloadmanager.service.port` is `8080`\n142: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n143: - **THEN** the Router container env includes `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://workloadmanager.agentcube.svc.cluster.local:8080`\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: Router health probes\n146: - **GIVEN** default values\n147: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n148: - **THEN** the Router container has liveness probe `httpGet /health/live` with `initialDelaySeconds: 1, periodSeconds: 2` and readiness probe `httpGet /health/ready` with `initialDelaySeconds: 1, periodSeconds: 2`\n149: \n150: #### Scenario: Router args include port and debug flag\n151: - **GIVEN** `router.service.targetPort` is `8080`\n152: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n153: - **THEN** the container args include `--port=8080` and `--debug`\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: Conditional serviceAccountName\n156: - **GIVEN** `--set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router`\n157: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n158: - **THEN** the Router Deployment `spec.template.spec.serviceAccountName` is `agentcube-router`\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: Empty serviceAccountName omits field\n161: - **GIVEN** `router.serviceAccountName` is `\"\"` (default)\n162: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n163: - **THEN** the Router Deployment does NOT set `serviceAccountName`\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Router extraEnv entries\n166: - **GIVEN** `--set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"LOG_LEVEL\",\"value\":\"debug\"}]'`\n167: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n168: - **THEN** the Router container env includes `LOG_LEVEL=debug`\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ### Requirement: Router Service template\n173: \n174: The template `agentcube-router.yaml` SHALL render a `Service` named `agentcube-router` with: `type` from `router.service.type`; `port` from `router.service.port`; `targetPort` from `router.service.targetPort`; selector `app: agentcube-router`.\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: Default router service renders\n177: - **GIVEN** default values\n178: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n179: - **THEN** a `Service` named `agentcube-router` exists with `type: ClusterIP`, `port: 8080`, `targetPort: 8080`, and selector `app: agentcube-router`\n180: \n181: ---\n182: \n183: ### Requirement: Workload Manager RBAC template\n184: \n185: The template `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` SHALL always render: a `ServiceAccount` named `workloadmanager` in the release namespace; a `ClusterRole` named `workloadmanager` with rules for agent-sandbox CRDs (`agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes`, `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxclaims`, `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxtemplates`, `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxwarmpools`, `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxwarmpools/status`), AgentCube CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters`, `codeinterpreters/status`, `codeinterpreters/finalizers`, `agentruntimes`, `agentruntimes/status`), core resources (`pods`, `secrets`), and auth (`authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews`); a `ClusterRoleBinding` named `workloadmanager` binding the ClusterRole to the ServiceAccount in the release namespace.\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: ServiceAccount renders in release namespace\n188: - **GIVEN** release namespace `agentcube`\n189: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n190: - **THEN** a `ServiceAccount` named `workloadmanager` exists in namespace `agentcube`\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: ClusterRole grants sandbox CRD permissions\n193: - **GIVEN** any valid installation\n194: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n195: - **THEN** the `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` includes rules granting `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` on `sandboxes` in `agents.x-k8s.io`\n196: \n197: #### Scenario: ClusterRole grants AgentCube CRD permissions\n198: - **GIVEN** any valid installation\n199: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n200: - **THEN** the `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` includes rules granting `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` on `codeinterpreters` in `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` and `get,list,watch` on `agentruntimes` in `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: ClusterRole grants status and finalizer permissions\n203: - **GIVEN** any valid installation\n204: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n205: - **THEN** the ClusterRole includes `get,update,patch` on `codeinterpreters/status`, `update` on `codeinterpreters/finalizers`, and `update,patch` on `agentruntimes/status`\n206: \n207: #### Scenario: ClusterRole grants secrets and tokenreview permissions\n208: - **GIVEN** any valid installation\n209: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n210: - **THEN** the ClusterRole includes full verbs on `secrets` in core API group and `create` on `tokenreviews` in `authentication.k8s.io`\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: ClusterRoleBinding ties SA to ClusterRole\n213: - **GIVEN** release namespace `agentcube`\n214: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n215: - **THEN** `ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager` has subject `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in namespace `agentcube` and roleRef `ClusterRole/workloadmanager`\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ### Requirement: Optional Router RBAC template\n220: \n221: The template `rbac-router.yaml` SHALL render **only if** `router.rbac.create` is true. When rendered, it SHALL create: a `ServiceAccount` named `{{ router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}` in the release namespace; a `Role` with the same name granting full verbs (`get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete`) on `secrets` in the release namespace; a `RoleBinding` binding the Role to the ServiceAccount.\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Router RBAC off by default\n224: - **GIVEN** `router.rbac.create: false` (default)\n225: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` is run\n226: - **THEN** no Router ServiceAccount, Role, or RoleBinding resources appear in the output\n227: \n228: #### Scenario: Router RBAC enabled\n229: - **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true`\n230: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n231: - **THEN** the output contains a `ServiceAccount`, `Role`, and `RoleBinding` for the Router, all named `agentcube-router` (default)\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Router RBAC with custom serviceAccountName\n234: - **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=my-router-sa`\n235: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n236: - **THEN** the ServiceAccount, Role, and RoleBinding are all named `my-router-sa`\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: Router Role grants secret management\n239: - **GIVEN** `--set router.rbac.create=true`\n240: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n241: - **THEN** the Router Role includes rule: apiGroup `\"\"`, resources `secrets`, verbs `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete`\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ### Requirement: Optional Volcano agent scheduler template\n246: \n247: The template `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` SHALL render **only if** `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true. When rendered, it SHALL create (in order): `ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler`; `ConfigMap/volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` with key `agent-scheduler.conf` (actions `allocate`, tiers with predicates and nodeorder); `ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler` with the full rule set from the deployment design; `ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role`; `Service/volcano-agent-scheduler-service` (port 8080, metrics annotations); `Deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler` with replicas from `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, image from `volcano.scheduler.image`, args including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, security contexts, and volumes for config + emptyDir.\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler disabled by default\n250: - **GIVEN** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (default)\n251: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` is run\n252: - **THEN** no Volcano scheduler resources appear in the output\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Volcano scheduler enabled\n255: - **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n256: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n257: - **THEN** the output contains ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, and Deployment for the Volcano scheduler\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: Volcano ConfigMap contains scheduler config\n260: - **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n261: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n262: - **THEN** `ConfigMap/volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` has key `agent-scheduler.conf` containing actions `allocate` and tiers with `predicates` and `nodeorder`\n263: \n264: #### Scenario: Volcano Deployment uses values for replicas and image\n265: - **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true --set volcano.scheduler.replicas=2 --set volcano.scheduler.image.tag=v1.0.0`\n266: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n267: - **THEN** the Volcano Deployment has `replicas: 2` and image `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler:v1.0.0`\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: Volcano Deployment args include scheduler name\n270: - **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n271: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n272: - **THEN** the Volcano container args include `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`\n273: \n274: #### Scenario: Volcano Service has metrics annotations\n275: - **GIVEN** `--set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n276: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n277: - **THEN** `Service/volcano-agent-scheduler-service` has port `8080` and Prometheus metrics annotations\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ### Requirement: CRDs shipped with chart\n282: \n283: The chart SHALL ship `CustomResourceDefinition` manifests under `crds/` directory: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` and `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml`. Both SHALL use API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, version `v1alpha1` (served and storage), and `scope: Namespaced`.\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD is present\n286: - **GIVEN** the chart directory `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n287: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base --include-crds` is run\n288: - **THEN** the output contains `CustomResourceDefinition/agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` with `spec.group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, `spec.versions` including `v1alpha1` as served and storage, and `scope: Namespaced`\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD is present\n291: - **GIVEN** the chart directory `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n292: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base --include-crds` is run\n293: - **THEN** the output contains `CustomResourceDefinition/codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` with `spec.group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`, `spec.versions` including `v1alpha1` as served and storage, and `scope: Namespaced`\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD required spec fields\n296: - **GIVEN** the AgentRuntime CRD YAML\n297: - **WHEN** its `openAPIV3Schema` is inspected\n298: - **THEN** `spec.required` includes `maxSessionDuration`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, and `targetPort`\n299: \n300: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD required spec fields\n301: - **GIVEN** the CodeInterpreter CRD YAML\n302: - **WHEN** its `openAPIV3Schema` is inspected\n303: - **THEN** `spec.required` includes `template` and `spec.authMode` defaults to `picod`\n304: \n305: ---\n306: \n307: ### Requirement: Helm install command with required values\n308: \n309: The chart SHALL support installation via `helm upgrade --install <release> manifests/charts/base --namespace <ns> --create-namespace` with `--set redis.addr=...` and optional `--set redis.password=...`. All component workloads SHALL render without manual editing of the output YAML.\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Install with minimal required values\n312: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with Helm 3\n313: - **WHEN** `helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube --create-namespace --set redis.addr=redis.agentcube.svc:6379 --set redis.password=pass --wait` succeeds\n314: - **THEN** Deployments `workloadmanager` and `agentcube-router`, Services, RBAC, and CRDs are all created in namespace `agentcube`\n315: \n316: #### Scenario: Install with component image overrides\n317: - **GIVEN** local images loaded into a Kind cluster\n318: - **WHEN** `helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base --namespace agentcube --create-namespace --set redis.addr=redis.agentcube.svc:6379 --set redis.password=\"\" --set workloadmanager.image.repository=workloadmanager --set workloadmanager.image.tag=latest --set router.image.repository=agentcube-router --set router.image.tag=latest --wait` succeeds\n319: - **THEN** Workload Manager and Router Deployments use the local image names and tags\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: Install with router RBAC and extraEnv\n322: - **GIVEN** a cluster with Helm 3\n323: - **WHEN** install includes `--set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=agentcube-router --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]'`\n324: - **THEN** Router RBAC resources are created and Router pods have the specified extraEnv\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ### Requirement: Helm upgrade preserves state\n329: \n330: The chart SHALL support upgrading an existing release with modified values without deleting existing resources (except where Helm's native upgrade semantics dictate replacement).\n331: \n332: #### Scenario: Upgrade replica count\n333: - **GIVEN** a release installed with default values (1 replica for Workload Manager)\n334: - **WHEN** `helm upgrade` is run with `--set workloadmanager.replicas=3`\n335: - **THEN** the Workload Manager Deployment is updated to `replicas: 3` without downtime (rolling update)\n336: \n337: #### Scenario: Upgrade image tag\n338: - **GIVEN** a release installed with `workloadmanager.image.tag=latest`\n339: - **WHEN** `helm upgrade` is run with `--set workloadmanager.image.tag=v1.1.0`\n340: - **THEN** the Workload Manager Deployment image is updated to `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:v1.1.0`\n341: \n342: ---\n343: \n344: ### Requirement: Helm template dry-run produces valid Kubernetes manifests\n345: \n346: The chart SHALL produce valid Kubernetes YAML when rendered with `helm template`, with no unresolved template variables and all required fields populated from defaults or overrides.\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: Default template output is valid\n349: - **GIVEN** default values\n350: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` is piped to `kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f -`\n351: - **THEN** no validation errors are reported\n352: \n353: #### Scenario: Template with all overrides is valid\n354: - **GIVEN** `--set redis.addr=redis.ns.svc:6379 --set redis.password=secret --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true --set router.rbac.create=true`\n355: - **WHEN** `helm template test manifests/charts/base` is piped to `kubectl apply --dry-run=client -f -`\n356: - **THEN** no validation errors are reported\n357: \n358: ---\n359: \n360: ### Requirement: Namespace scoping via Release.Namespace\n361: \n362: All namespaced resources SHALL use `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` for their namespace field, not hardcoded values.\n363: \n364: #### Scenario: Workload Manager Deployment uses release namespace\n365: - **GIVEN** `--namespace production`\n366: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n367: - **THEN** the Workload Manager Deployment has `metadata.namespace: production`\n368: \n369: #### Scenario: Router Service uses release namespace\n370: - **GIVEN** `--namespace staging`\n371: - **WHEN` templates are rendered\n372: - **THEN** the Router Service has `metadata.namespace: staging`\n373: \n374: ---\n375: \n376: ### Requirement: nameOverride and fullnameOverride support\n377: \n378: The chart SHALL support `nameOverride` and `fullnameOverride` values for customizing resource names, following Helm naming conventions.\n379: \n380: #### Scenario: Default naming convention\n381: - **GIVEN** default values and release name `my-release`\n382: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n383: - **THEN** resource names follow the chart's default naming (e.g., `workloadmanager`, `agentcube-router`)\n384: \n385: #### Scenario: fullnameOverride renames resources\n386: - **GIVEN** `--set fullnameOverride=agentcube-prod`\n387: - **WHEN** templates are rendered\n388: - **THEN** applicable resource names use `agentcube-prod` as the base name\n389: \n390: ## File Changes\n391: \n392: | Action | File | Description |\n393: |--------|------|-------------|\n394: | Create | `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Chart metadata (apiVersion v1, name agentcube, version 0.1.0, appVersion 1.0.0) |\n395: | Create | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Default configuration values for all components (Redis, Router, Workload Manager, Volcano) |\n396: | Create | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | Workload Manager Deployment + Service with health probes, Redis env vars, extraEnv |\n397: | Create | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Router Deployment + Service with health probes, WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL, conditional serviceAccountName |\n398: | Create | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Workload Manager ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding |\n399: | Create | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Optional Router ServiceAccount + Role + RoleBinding (gated by router.rbac.create) |\n400: | Create | `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` | Optional Volcano scheduler resources (gated by volcano.scheduler.enabled) |\n401: | Create | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | AgentRuntime CRD (group runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh, v1alpha1, Namespaced) |\n402: | Create | `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | CodeInterpreter CRD (group runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh, v1alpha1, Namespaced) |\n\n(End of file - total 402 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `manifests`\n- **Language:** YAML\n- **Size:** L\n- **Base specs:** `deployment/spec.md`, `deployment/design.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Chart.yaml metadata\n\nThe chart SHALL define `Chart.yaml` with `apiVersion: v1`, `name: agentcube`, `version: 0.1.0`, and `appVersion: 1.0.0`.\n\n#### Scenario: Chart metadata fields are correct\n- **GIVEN** the file `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** it is parsed as YAML\n- **THEN** `apiVersion` equals `v1`, `name` equals `agentcube`, `version` equals `0.1.0`, and `appVersion` equals `1.0.0`\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775870573895,"end":1775870573902}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870575127,"sessionID":"ses_285e13ecaffeMp9o3UxFFIXU67","part":{"id":"prt_d7a227dd7001dMkdLhdlBb79qe","messageID":"msg_d7a225cf7001neUFjYw8W3JQWZ","sessionID":"ses_285e13ecaffeMp9o3UxFFIXU67","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a67476aebae14d458a9a7d2e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Design\n2: \n3: Source tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n4: \n5: ## Chart.yaml\n6: \n7: | Field | Value |\n8: |--------|--------|\n9: | `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n10: | `name` | `agentcube` |\n11: | `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n12: | `version` | `0.1.0` |\n13: | `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n14: \n15: ## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n16: \n17: | Path | Type | Default |\n18: |------|------|---------|\n19: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n20: | `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n21: | `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n22: | `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` |\n23: | `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` |\n24: | `router.replicas` | int | `1` |\n25: | `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` |\n26: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n27: | `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n28: | `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n29: | `router.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n30: | `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` |\n31: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n32: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n33: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n34: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n35: | `router.config` | object | `{}` |\n36: | `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n37: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` |\n38: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` |\n39: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` |\n40: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` |\n41: | `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n42: | `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n43: | `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n44: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n45: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n46: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n47: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n48: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n49: | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n50: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` |\n51: | `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` |\n52: | `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` |\n53: | `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n54: | `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n55: \n56: Comments in `values.yaml` state Redis settings “must be provided by the user during installation”; defaults are still empty strings.\n57: \n58: ## Template files (`manifests/charts/base/templates/`)\n59: \n60: ### `workloadmanager.yaml`\n61: \n62: | Kind | Name | Namespace | Notes |\n63: |------|------|-----------|--------|\n64: | `Deployment` | `workloadmanager` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` | `replicas`: `workloadmanager.replicas`; `serviceAccountName`: `workloadmanager`; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `workloadmanager`; image `repository:tag`; `imagePullPolicy`; port `http` → `workloadmanager.service.port`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef `metadata.namespace`), `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_ADDR`, plus `workloadmanager.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, `--runtime-class-name=` (empty); **resources**: from values; **liveness/readiness**: HTTP GET `/health` on service port, delays 10s/10s and 5s/5s |\n65: | `Service` | `workloadmanager` | release ns | `type`: `workloadmanager.service.type`; port & `targetPort`: `workloadmanager.service.port`; selector `app: workloadmanager` |\n66: \n67: ### `agentcube-router.yaml`\n68: \n69: | Kind | Name | Notes |\n70: |------|------|--------|\n71: | `Deployment` | `agentcube-router` | `replicas`: `router.replicas`; **conditional** `serviceAccountName` if `router.serviceAccountName` non-empty; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `agentcube-router`; image from `router.image`; container port `router.service.targetPort`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, plus `router.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug`; **resources** from values; **liveness** `/health/live`, **readiness** `/health/ready` on targetPort, 1s initial, 2s period |\n72: | `Service` | `agentcube-router` | `type` `router.service.type`; `port` `router.service.port`, `targetPort` `router.service.targetPort`; selector `app: agentcube-router` |\n73: \n74: ### `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n75: \n76: | Kind | Name | Scope | Notes |\n77: |------|------|-------|--------|\n78: | `ServiceAccount` | `workloadmanager` | release namespace | — |\n79: | `ClusterRole` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | rules below |\n80: | `ClusterRoleBinding` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | binds `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` to `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in release namespace |\n81: \n82: ### `rbac-router.yaml`\n83: \n84: Rendered **only if** `router.rbac.create` is true.\n85: \n86: | Kind | Name pattern | Notes |\n87: |------|--------------|--------|\n88: | `ServiceAccount` | `{{ router.serviceAccountName \\| default \"agentcube-router\" }}` | release namespace |\n89: | `Role` | same as SA name | rules: `secrets` in `\"\"` apiGroup, full verb set `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n90: | `RoleBinding` | same | subject: SA above; `Role` ref same name |\n91: \n92: ### `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n93: \n94: Rendered **only if** `volcano.scheduler.enabled`.\n95: \n96: Creates (in order in file): `ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler`; `ConfigMap/volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` with key `agent-scheduler.conf` (actions `allocate`, tiers predicates/nodeorder); `ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler` (large rule set — see RBAC section); `ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role`; `Service/volcano-agent-scheduler-service` (port 8080 metrics annotations); `Deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler` with `replicas` from `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, image from values, args including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, security contexts, volumes for config + emptyDir.\n97: \n98: ## RBAC rules (exact apiGroups / resources / verbs)\n99: \n100: ### ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n101: \n102: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n103: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n104: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n105: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n106: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n107: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n108: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n109: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n110: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n111: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n112: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n113: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n114: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n115: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n116: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n117: \n118: ### Role `router` (optional)\n119: \n120: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n121: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n122: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n123: \n124: ### ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` (when enabled)\n125: \n126: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n127: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n128: | `apiextensions.k8s.io` | `customresourcedefinitions` | `create,get,list,watch,delete` |\n129: | `\"\"` | `events` | `create,list,watch,update,patch` |\n130: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch,patch,delete` |\n131: | `\"\"` | `pods/status` | `update` |\n132: | `\"\"` | `pods/binding` | `create` |\n133: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumeclaims` | `list,watch,update` |\n134: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumes` | `list,watch,update` |\n135: | `\"\"` | `namespaces,services,replicationcontrollers` | `list,watch,get` |\n136: | `\"\"` | `resourcequotas` | `list,watch` |\n137: | `\"\"` | `nodes` | `get,list,watch,update,patch` |\n138: | `storage.k8s.io` | `storageclasses,csinodes,csidrivers,csistoragecapacities,volumeattachments` | `list,watch` |\n139: | `policy` | `poddisruptionbudgets` | `list,watch` |\n140: | `scheduling.k8s.io` | `priorityclasses` | `get,list,watch` |\n141: | `scheduling.incubator.k8s.io`, `scheduling.volcano.sh` | `podgroups` | `list,watch,update` |\n142: | `\"\"` | `configmaps` | `get,list,watch,create,delete,update` |\n143: | `apps` | `daemonsets,replicasets,statefulsets` | `list,watch,get` |\n144: | `coordination.k8s.io` | `leases` | `get,create,update,watch` |\n145: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch` |\n146: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims/status` | `update` |\n147: | `resource.k8s.io` | `deviceclasses,resourceslices` | `get,list,watch,create` |\n148: | `shard.volcano.sh` | `nodeshards` | `list,watch,get,update` |\n149: \n150: ## CRD definitions shipped (`manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n151: \n152: | File | CRD `metadata.name` | group | versions | scope | Notes |\n153: |------|---------------------|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n154: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` (served+storage); printer column Age | `Namespaced` | `openAPIV3Schema` includes root fields `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`, `status`. **spec.required**: `maxSessionDuration`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`. **Key spec fields**: `maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`); `sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`); `targetPort` (array of port objects: required `port`, `protocol` enum HTTP/HTTPS, optional `name`, `pathPrefix`); `podTemplate` (annotations, labels, nested `spec` = full PodSpec-shaped schema). **status**: conditions, etc. Annotation `controller-gen.kubebuilder.io/version: v0.17.2` |\n155: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `Namespaced` | **spec** includes `authMode` enum `picod|none` default `picod`; `maxSessionDuration` default `8h`; `sessionTimeout` default `15m`; `ports` (same TargetPort shape as above); `template` (image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.); optional `warmPoolSize` int32. **spec.required**: `template`. **status**: `conditions`, `ready`; subresource `status`. Same controller-gen version annotation |\n156: \n157: ## Dockerfiles\n158: \n159: ### `docker/Dockerfile` (workloadmanager)\n160: \n161: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n162: |-------|------|---------|\n163: | builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | `WORKDIR /workspace`; copy `go.mod`/`go.sum`; `go mod download`; copy `cmd/`, `pkg/`; build `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` with BuildKit cache mounts |\n164: | runtime | `alpine:3.19` | `apk add ca-certificates`; `WORKDIR /app`; copy binary; `adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver`; `USER apiserver`; `EXPOSE 8080`; `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]`; `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]` |\n165: \n166: Build args: `TARGETOS=linux`, `TARGETARCH` (implicit platform).\n167: \n168: ### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n169: \n170: Same pattern as workloadmanager builder, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/`; output binary `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router`; runtime user `router` UID 1000; `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`.\n171: \n172: ### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n173: \n174: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n175: |-------|------|---------|\n176: | builder | `golang:1.24.4` | `WORKDIR /app`; copy mod files; download; `COPY . .`; build `picod` from `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` |\n177: | runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` | `apt-get install -y python3`; `WORKDIR /root/`; copy binary; **runs as root** (comment: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions); `ENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]` |\n178: \n179: ## Makefile — variables (key)\n180: \n181: | Variable | Default / definition |\n182: |----------|----------------------|\n183: | `HUB` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` |\n184: | `TAG` | `latest` |\n185: | `PROJECT_DIR` | directory of Makefile |\n186: | `GOBIN` | from `go env` |\n187: | `CONTAINER_TOOL` | `docker` |\n188: | `SHELL` | `/usr/bin/env bash -o pipefail` |\n189: | `LOCALBIN` | `$(shell pwd)/bin` |\n190: | `CONTROLLER_GEN` | `$(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen` |\n191: | `GOLANGCI_LINT` | `$(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint` |\n192: | `CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION` | `v0.17.2` |\n193: | `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `v1.64.1` |\n194: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n195: | `ROUTER_IMAGE` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n196: | `PICOD_IMAGE` | `picod:latest` |\n197: | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `\"\"` |\n198: | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | `agentcube-e2e` |\n199: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_REPO` | `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox.git` |\n200: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION` | `main` (Makefile comment; E2E script overrides — see CI design) |\n201: \n202: ## Makefile — targets\n203: \n204: | Target | Depends / notes |\n205: |--------|-----------------|\n206: | `all` | → `build` |\n207: | `help` | awk help from `##` comments |\n208: | `gen-crd` | `controller-gen`; `crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` → `manifests/charts/base/crds` |\n209: | `generate` | `controller-gen object` + `gen-crd` + `go mod tidy` |\n210: | `gen-client` | `bash hack/update-codegen.sh`; `go mod tidy` |\n211: | `gen-all` | `generate` + `gen-client` |\n212: | `gen-check` | `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code` |\n213: | `build` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` |\n214: | `build-agentd` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` |\n215: | `build-router` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router` |\n216: | `build-all` | `build` + `build-agentd` + `build-router` |\n217: | `run` | `go run ./cmd/workload-manager/main.go --port=8080 --ssh-username=sandbox --ssh-port=22` |\n218: | `run-local` | same with `--kubeconfig=${HOME}/.kube/config` |\n219: | `run-router` | `go run ./cmd/router/main.go --port=8080 --debug` |\n220: | `clean` | `rm -rf bin/` and root binaries |\n221: | `deps` | `go mod download`; `go mod tidy` |\n222: | `update-deps` | `go get -u ./...`; `go mod tidy` |\n223: | `test` | `go test -v ./...` |\n224: | `fmt` | `go fmt ./...` |\n225: | `vet` | `go vet ./...` |\n226: | `lint` | `$(GOLANGCI_LINT) run ./...` |\n227: | `gen-copyright` | `hack/update-copyright.sh` |\n228: | `install` | `build` + `sudo cp bin/workloadmanager /usr/local/bin/` |\n229: | `docker-build` | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n230: | `docker-buildx` | buildx linux/amd64,arm64 |\n231: | `docker-buildx-push` | requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY`; buildx `--push` |\n232: | `docker-push` | tag+push workloadmanager |\n233: | `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE)` |\n234: | `docker-build-router` / `docker-buildx-router` / `docker-buildx-push-router` / `docker-push-router` / `kind-load-router` | same pattern for router image |\n235: | `docker-build-picod` / `docker-buildx-picod` / `docker-buildx-push-picod` / `docker-push-picod` | same for picod |\n236: | `controller-gen` / `golangci-lint` | download via `go-install-tool` macro |\n237: | `e2e` | `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n238: | `e2e-clean` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n239: | `build-python-sdk` | copy `LICENSE` to `sdk-python`, `python3 -m build` in `sdk-python`, remove copied LICENSE |\n240: \n241: ## hack/ scripts\n242: \n243: | File | Purpose |\n244: |------|---------|\n245: | `hack/update-codegen.sh` | Runs `k8s.io/code-generator` **v0.34.1**: sources `kube_codegen.sh`, calls `kube::codegen::gen_client --with-watch --output-dir client-go --output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go --boilerplate hack/boilerplate.go.txt --one-input-api runtime/v1alpha1` on `pkg/apis`; post-processes lister files with `sed` to append `.GroupResource()` for codeinterpreter/agentruntime resources |\n246: | `hack/update-copyright.sh` | Prepends Apache/Volcano boilerplate to `*.go` and `*.py` under git root (excluding vendor/venv) if missing “Copyright The Volcano Authors”; uses `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` / `hack/boilerplate.py.txt`; requires `sponge` (moreutils) |\n247: | `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` | Go file header template |\n248: | `hack/boilerplate.py.txt` | Python file header template |\n249: \n250: ## Helm / E2E reference command (from `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n251: \n252: Illustrative install used in E2E:\n253: \n254: ```bash\n255: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n256:   --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n257:   --create-namespace \\\n258:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n259:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n260:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n261:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n262:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"},{\"name\":\"JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE\",\"value\":\"agentcube\"}]' \\\n263:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n264:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n265:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n266:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n267:   --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n268:   --wait\n269: ```\n270: \n271: Images are expected to be loaded into Kind with local names `workloadmanager:latest`, `agentcube-router:latest`, `picod:latest` after `make docker-build` variants.\n\n(End of file - total 271 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Design\n\nSource tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n\n## Chart.yaml\n\n| Field | Value |\n|--------|--------|\n| `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n| `name` | `agentcube` |\n| `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n| `version` | `0.1.0` |\n| `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n\n## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n\n| Path | Type | Default |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n| `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/design.md","time":{"start":1775870575120,"end":1775870575125}}}}
